You should see output showing the installed Java version.

üîß 5. Set Up a Code Editor or IDE
Install an IDE for writing and running Java code easily:

IntelliJ IDEA (Highly recommended for beginners)
Eclipse (Great for large projects)
Visual Studio Code (Lightweight with Java extensions)
üöÄ 6. Write and Run Your First Java Program
Try running a simple Java program to confirm everything works:

Create a new file called HelloWorld.java.
Paste this code:
java
Copy
Edit
public class HelloWorld {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Java is successfully set up!");
    }
}
Open terminal/command prompt, navigate to the file location, and run:
